Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Health and Welfare to
the original bill:
1. Remove the requirement to obtain patient consent to record for the purpose of
transcribing a conversation between a healthcare professional and a patient using
artificial intelligence.
2. Remove the option for the patient to opt out of being recorded during an
appointment or treatment for the purpose of transcribing a conversation between
a healthcare professional and a patient using artificial intelligence.
3. Make technical changes.
